steps.description:
You'll need an electric motor or similar type rotary motor that runs on at least 12 volts; 18 volts would be ideal. The motor will have a small shaft protruding from the center. Take a small four-hole button and attach it to that shaft with superglue. Be careful not to use so much glue that it seeps through the holes of the button and blocks them. They need to be open so that you can attach the needle. Set it aside to dry. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/db/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/db/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
Instead of a button, you can use an eraser. Take the eraser from a mechanical pen and push it firmly onto the small shaft of your motor. You can remove the motor from a VCR or remote control car, but the power will be considerably less; it's about 3.5 volts. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/74/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/74/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

The "tube" will guide the needle. It's easy to make one from a pencil or pen. Use a mechanical pencil. An inexpensive plastic pencil will work fine, or you can choose one that's metal. Depending on your preference, you can leave the pencil as-is or cut it down to about a 3" to 4" length. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Alternately, you can use an everyday stick pen like a Bic and remove the ink cylinder from inside. If you want a shorter tube, cut the pen to about a 3" or 4" length. File down the brass tip of the pen to get the ball out and make the hole big enough to allow passage of the needle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5d/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5d/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

The brace will support the tube when it's attached to the machine motor for the tattoo gun. Take a teaspoon and break off the bowl (the part you eat from). Then bend the spoon back to create an "L"-shape. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

A second option would be to cut the bristles off of a toothbrush leaving about 4" in length. Use a lighter to heat up the plastic toothbrush handle and bend it into an "L" shape. Hold the bent handle in place until the plastic cools, and it becomes stiff. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Home-Made-Tattoo-Gun-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
